                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_318-item1">
                     <author key="person_2860572">Lethbert of Saint-Ruf</author>
                     <title key="work_2974">Flores psalmorum</title>
                     <rubric>Flores Psalterii</rubric>
                     <note>A commentary on the whole Psalter, with two prologues and later marginal notes</note>
                     <note>The first prologue is from 'Galterus Magolonensis episcopus' sending this work to Rogerus, Insulanus praepositus, and explaining that 
                        it is a cento from Augustine, Cassiodorus, and others collected by Lethbertus 'olim canonicus vester postmodum sancti Rufi abbas', 
                        but the parts collected from each writer cannot be distinguished</note>
                     <note>The work is divided into three parts, see fols 79v, 154</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  
